casebody.data:
Raquel HOPPER, Appellant,
v.
HNB NATIONAL BANK and One Home Realty, Inc., Respondents. WD 81831 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: April 2, 2019 Michael Mohlman, Kansas City, MO, Counsel for Appellant, Hopper. Rachel Smith, Kansas City, MO, Co-Counsel for Appellant, Hopper. Michael Waddell, Overland Park, KS, Co-Counsel for Appellant, Hopper. John Davidson, Overland Park, KS, Counsel for Respondent, HNB National Bank. Peter Collins, Overland Park, KS, Co-Counsel for Respondent, HNB National Bank. Jennifer Rose, Lee's Summit, MO, Counsel for Respondent, One Home Realty, Inc. Before Division One: Cynthia L. Martin, P.J., Thomas H. Newton, and Gary D. Witt, JJ.

ORDER

Per Curiam:

Ms. Raquel Hopper appeals a Buchanan County Circuit Court judgment sustaining HNB National Bank's motion for summary judgment and One Home Realty, Inc.'s motion to dismiss in this negligence action arising from a personal injury caused by a dog bite. For reasons stated in the memorandum provided to the parties, we affirm. Rule 84.16(b).
